  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This UoA evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Intended use is confined to pre-market design-space screening of hemolysis risk under nominal CPB flow conditions (3–6 L/min, 60–120 mmHg differential pressure) and does not extend to patient-specific surgical planning or post-market surveillance.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/fda-gcbp-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-gcbp-piv-experimental",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-gcbp-hemolysis-bench"
  ],
